HEADWORD: Chronoscope
<hw>Chron"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ time +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring minute
intervals of time; used in determining the velocity of projectiles, the
duration of short-lived luminous phenomena, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chrysalid</ent>⟦br⟧
